### Default & Risk Management (Your Updated View)

- **Default Impact on User**:


  - Permanent damage to reputation score in your oracle (publicly visible).
  - Cannot borrow again from you or participating lenders.
  - Loses access to better terms and higher LTVs in the entire SOS ecosystem.

- **Your Side as Root Lender**:


  - You **keep the collateral value** in the system (the SOS balance stays in the user’s address but is now “tainted” and less liquid/valuable on the secondary market).
  - You can optionally **pay back small lenders** from your own capital to protect their trust and maintain the lending pool’s reputation.
  - **System-level gain**: The ecosystem retains the SOS tokens in circulation. You (or the market) can later acquire defaulted high-balance addresses at a discount via account sales because of the damaged reputation.
  - Gas efficiency note: You mentioned gaining extra SOS “by 50% cheaper gas cost” — this can be interpreted as lower effective acquisition cost when buying defaulted or distressed accounts (cheaper than pushing equivalent new volume yourself).

This structure strongly incentivizes repayment (reputation = future borrowing power + higher wallet value) while giving you downside protection and accumulation upside.

